</td><td>Renamed: 'Data collection; management; and use' → 'Data Management'</td></tr><tr><td>4.1.1</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#inexact\" title=\"inexact\">maps loosely to</a></td><td>4.1.1</td><td>v1: 'Non-routine data collection and management'; v2: 'Form creation for data acquisition' — overlapping but distinct scope</td></tr><tr><td>4.1.2</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.1.2</td><td/></tr><tr><td>4.1.3</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.1.3</td><td>Renamed: 'visualisation' → 'visualizations'</td></tr><tr><td>4.1.4</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.1.4</td><td>Scope extended to explicitly include AI and machine learning</td></tr><tr><td>4.2</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.2</td><td/></tr><tr><td>4.2.1</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.2.1</td><td/></tr><tr><td>4.2.2</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.2.2</td><td/></tr><tr><td>4.2.3</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.2.3</td><td/></tr><tr><td>4.3</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.3</td><td>Renamed: 'Location mapping' → 'Geo spatial information management'; expanded from 4 to 5 sub-codes</td></tr><tr><td>4.3.1</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.3.1</td><td>Expanded: 'Map location of health facilities/structures' → '...and households'</td></tr><tr><td>4.3.2</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.3.2</td><td>Renamed: 'Map location of health events' → 'Map location of health event'</td></tr><tr><td>4.3.3</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.3.3</td><td>Renamed: 'clients and households' → 'persons and settlements'</td></tr><tr><td>4.3.4</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.3.4</td><td>Renamed: 'health worker' → 'healthcare provider[s]'</td></tr><tr><td>4.4</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#equivalent\" title=\"equivalent\">is equivalent to</a></td><td>4.4</td><td>Renamed: 'Data exchange and interoperability'; split from 1 leaf code into 3 in v2</td></tr><tr><td>4.4.1</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#wider\" title=\"wider\">maps to wider concept</a></td><td>4.4.1</td><td>v1 'Data exchange across systems' is broader; v2 4.4.1 covers only point-to-point integration. See also v2 4.4.2 [standards-compliant] and 4.4.3 [message routing].</td></tr><tr><td>4.4.1</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#wider\" title=\"wider\">maps to wider concept</a></td><td>4.4.2</td><td>v2 4.4.2 'Standards-compliant interoperability' partially covers the broader v1 4.4.1 concept</td></tr><tr><td>4.4.1</td><td><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/R5/codesystem-concept-map-relationship.html#wider\" title=\"wider\">maps to wider concept</a></td><td>4.4.3</td><td>v2 4.4.3 'Message routing' partially covers the broader v1 4.4.1 concept</td></tr></table></div></div>"^^rdf:XMLLiteral ]
